Description: Up for auction is one owner KNAGGS Tier 2 HONGA model, 24 fret electric guitar in like new, mint condition. The color is called winter snow. I, the seller, and first owner of this guitar purchased this model KNAGGS guitar new in June 2018. I have played it only occasionally in my smoke free home. It has not been taken out of the home since time of purchase. It weighs approximately 6.8 pounds It has Kluson tuners, a bone nut, Dunlop strap buttons and gold hardware. Electronic's include two, Seth Lover humbucking pick ups, two volumes controls, two tone controls and a three way toggle switch. This KNAGGS guitar, per the build sheet, indicates that it was completed on August 31, 2017 and is serial number 5. Included in the sale is the original hardshell case and a set of Dunlap strap locks that came with the guitar. There are no known issues with this guitar that I am aware of. There is a few very faint lines/swirl marks on the bottom of the pic guard near the controls which can be noted in the last photo. Thanks for looking and good luck. Knaggs Honga info made 8/17  The Knaggs Influence Honga model is a double cutaway with a contoured top and back, three on a side headstock, and a 24.75″ scale. Designed and built by famed builder Joe Knaggs Knaggs’ proprietary Influence hard-tail designed to allow for increased string vibration and sustain. Title: KNAGGS TIER 2 HONGA CUTAWAY GUITAR 24 FRETS WINTER SNOW
